After making a change, advise the user on how to test changes in the front end. Explain what flow they should follow, and what to look for to validate success.

After the user confirms changes look good, and are ready to proceed:

Use docs/next-task-agent-prompt.md after a task is completed to create instructions for the next agent's task. Make sure all outstanding tasks are completed before overwriting the doc, and call out any risks/missed content to the user so that the next agent can pick it up. 

Create a prompt to copy to the next agent, as well as a title for the current agent to summarize its task (3-5 words max). Include the followup prompt and agent title in the agent chat, not the .md file. 

Include in the copy-paste prompt a link to NEXT-AGENT-TASK.md
